HEADWORD: Ischial
<hw>Is"chi*al</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧s"k⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the ischium or hip; ischiac;
ischiadic; ischiatic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ischial callosity</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>one
of the patches of thickened, hairless, and often bright-colored skin, on
the buttocks of many apes, as the drill.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 791 --></p>

<p><ent>Ischiatic</ent>⟦br⟧
